description: A square temple located about half a mile north-east of the town in a temenos. Lewis (1966) suggests a chronology from the late 2nd or early 3rd CE to the mid or late 4th CE.
bibliography: Clarke, R. R. “Roman Britain in 1957.” Journal of Roman Studies 48 (1958): 142.
Clarke Rainbird, R. “Archaeological Discoveries in Norfolk, 1949-54.” Norfolk Archaeology 31 (1955): 404.
Wright, R. P. “Roman Britain in 1956: I. Sites Explored: II. Inscriptions.” Journal of Roman Studies 47 (1957): 211.
